  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About This Archive</h1>

    <p>
      This website is a personal memorial and research archive dedicated to the life of
      <strong>Herman (Zvi) Freiman</strong> — my grandfather, a Holocaust survivor from
      Boryslaw, Galicia (Nowadays Ukraine).
    </p>

    <p>
      The archive brings together documentary evidence from the Arolsen Archives (ITS),
      Yad Vashem, and personal family photographs, alongside historical context about
      the Jewish community of Boryslaw and the events of the Holocaust in eastern Galicia.
      It is a work in progress, and will continue to grow as new sources are found.
    </p>

    <h2>About Me</h2>

    <p>
      My name is <strong>Sharon Fraiman</strong>. I am Herman's grandson, based in Israel, Kiryat-Ata.
      I created this archive to preserve what is known of his story, and share it with the rest of my family.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you have information, documents, photographs, or family connections related to
      Herman Freiman or the Freiman / Frajman / Fraiman family of Boryslaw, I would very much like
      to hear from you.
    </p>

    <p>
      You can reach me at: <a href="mailto:sfsharon@gmail.com">sfsharon@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
